<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>You Learned: Log Analysis</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/learn.css">
</head>
<body>
  <div class="learn-page">
    <img src="/images/logo.png" alt="EECS Girls Who Tech Camp" class="learn-logo">

    <div class="learn-hero">
      <div class="hero-icon">📋</div>
      <h1>Challenge 5 Complete!</h1>
      <p class="hero-subtitle">Log Detective</p>
      <div class="flag-badge"><%= flag %></div>
    </div>

    <div class="learn-grid">
      <div class="learn-card skill-card">
        <div class="card-icon">🔍</div>
        <h2>Skill Unlocked</h2>
        <h3>Log Analysis + Base64</h3>
        <p>You analyzed server logs to spot suspicious patterns, then decoded a Base64 string. Base64 is <strong>encoding, not encryption</strong> — it's trivially reversible!</p>
      </div>

      <div class="learn-card world-card">
        <div class="card-icon">🌍</div>
        <h2>Real World</h2>
        <h3>Incident Response</h3>
        <p>When a company gets hacked, the security team's first move is examining logs. Tools like Splunk and ELK Stack monitor millions of log entries in real time.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="learn-card career-card">
        <div class="card-icon">👩‍💻</div>
        <h2>Career Path</h2>
        <h3>SOC Analyst</h3>
        <p>Security Operations Center analysts monitor networks 24/7, detecting and responding to threats. High demand, excellent pay, and curiosity matters more than degrees.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="learn-card key-card">
        <div class="card-icon">🔑</div>
        <h2>Key Takeaway</h2>
        <h3>Patterns Tell Stories</h3>
        <p>Suspicious patterns — probing <code>/admin</code>, <code>/.env</code>, <code>/backup.sql</code> — are red flags. Pattern recognition and attention to detail are superpowers in security.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="learn-nav">
      <a href="/" class="nav-btn secondary">← All Challenges</a>
      <% if (hasNext) { %>
      <a href="/challenge/<%= nextNum %>" class="nav-btn primary">Next Challenge →</a>
      <% } %>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
